Where do I begin? I'll start with the excellent and flawless service each time you come to the cart. There is an organic familial feel when you encounter Ms. Tami and her staff. I always compare it to being in my Auntie's kitchen during Thanksgiving meal prep! All the bites are mouth watering but if I had to highlight my favorites it would be -Shrimp & Grits -Wings & Waffles -Whiting Po-Boy -Mac-n-Cheese bites No matter what day of the week or time of day I patronize, the food is always consistently delicious! I go back again and again because comfort food and dynamic conversation are an additive to the experience. It is clear that Tami and her staff have a passion for what they do. It shows in every meal prepared.  Eboni N. Harlem, NY

This was the most pleasant surprise I've had in a while. The food is simply perfect, nothing else to say about it. The service is beyond fantastic! The lady that makes and serves the food is so friendly, that you'll fall in love. Even if you're in a rush, take a break to enjoy this awesome food truck experience. Loved it!

I was in NYC for a week celebrating my 10th year wedding anniversary. On our last day in the city we decided to go back to Harlem and do some shopping and enjoy an outdoor concert. It was here where I smelled the most wonderful aroma of fried fish and decided to patronize this business. The wait was over 20 mins which was expected because of how many people were in line. But what wasn't expected was to be cursed out for getting ketchup and  hot sauce for food that I purchased from the business and was readily available and offered to me when I got my food. I was called everything but a child of God by the chef and threatened to have my hand chopped off because she "didn't know what I was reaching for". I have read the reviews and heard that she has such a beautiful soul, I just wish I had met that part of her that day. Her gift of cooking is undeniable but you can lose everything because of character flaws.

I ate everything on the menu and everything is made fresh to order. I love her authenticity she is truly a mother and aunt to many. I feel like I knew her my whole life. Thank you for sharing your greatness.

The food was good but the chef has a very nasty mouth. She curses at people that walk past and go to other vendors. I personally have seen her on 21st ST multiple times being very disrespectful. She cursed at me and called me various names because she messed my order up and I asked her about it. She threatened to throw hot oil on me and she told me she can do that because she was famous from being on "POWER"... She thinks it's cute but customer service is very important.

So as I was parking there was a food truck on the sidewalk. I walked around and saw it’s blacked owned. Of course I want to support and purchased fish and vegan tacos. I was skeptical because didn’t care for whitings or lettuce but the hustler came out of the owner and convinced me to get it anyway. She was very nice about it and wasn’t pushy or forcing me to get it. The vegan taco was superb, very shockingly good lol. My cousin loved the whiting and it was her first time. She said it was very different and good. #SupportBlack #TryIt #NoRegrets
